<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070902071240/http://www.historynet.com/exploration/westward_expansion/3035001.html">Martin Company: Mormon Pioneers Used Handcarts to Trek to Salt Lake City</a> article by Sherman L. Fleek</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20181010225156/https://handcartpageant.com/">The Mormon Handcart Pageant</a> – A theatrical re-enactment, dedicated to the Martin and Willie Handcart Companies of 1856 and their Rescuers, both past and present.</li></ul>
